body:
The compile time Python version is allowed to be older when using the Limited API / stable ABI.

Closes https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5689

comment_data.body: We could probably also use the runtime version hex to get rid of this code, but it's currently generated too early. I don't see a reason to put the implementation so high up here, though. The prototype should be enough.
`__PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX` instead of `Py_VERSION_HEX` I think. They're equivalent in regular mode, but in limited API mode it's the version of limited API you're using
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -3076,7 +3076,8 @@ def generate_module_init_func(self, imported_modules, env, code):
         code.put_setup_refcount_context(header3)
 
         env.use_utility_code(UtilityCode.load("CheckBinaryVersion", "ModuleSetupCode.c"))
-        code.put_error_if_neg(self.pos, "__Pyx_check_binary_version()")
+        code.put_error_if_neg(
+            self.pos, "__Pyx_check_binary_version(PY_VERSION_HEX, __Pyx_get_runtime_version(), CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API)")

@@ -3076,7 +3076,8 @@ def generate_module_init_func(self, imported_modules, env, code):
         code.put_setup_refcount_context(header3)
 
         env.use_utility_code(UtilityCode.load("CheckBinaryVersion", "ModuleSetupCode.c"))
-        code.put_error_if_neg(self.pos, "__Pyx_check_binary_version()")
+        code.put_error_if_neg(
+            self.pos, "__Pyx_check_binary_version(PY_VERSION_HEX, __Pyx_get_runtime_version(), CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API)")

commit.message:
Implement a better check for the import time Python version against the compile time Python version that also accepts later versions when using the Limited API / stable ABI.

Closes https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5689
Use "__PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX" for compile time version checking.

title: Implement a better check for the import time Python version
